  "prompt": "What is the name of Santa Claus in other countries?",
  "response": "Santa Claus is known by various names around the world, reflecting cultural differences and local traditions. Here are some examples:\n\n1. **United Kingdom**: Father Christmas\n2. **Germany**: Weihnachtsmann\n3. **France**: P\u00e8re No\u00ebl\n4. **Spain**: Pap\u00e1 Noel\n5. **Italy**: Babbo Natale\n6. **Netherlands**: Sinterklaas\n7. **Sweden**: Jultomten\n8. **Norway**: Julenissen\n9. **Russia**: Ded Moroz (Father Frost)\n10. **Japan**: Santa-san or \u30b5\u30f3\u30bf\u30af\u30ed\u30fc\u30b9 (Santa Kur\u014dsu)\n11. **Brazil**: Papai Noel\n12. **China**: \u5723\u8bde\u8001\u4eba (Sh\u00e8ngd\u00e0n L\u01ceor\u00e9n, meaning \"Christmas Old Man\")\n13. **Mexico**: Pap\u00e1 Noel\n14. **Finland**: Joulupukki\n15. **Greece**: Agios Vasilios (Saint Basil)\n\nThese names may come with unique local customs and stories related to the holiday season.",
